---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Barbados Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/barbados/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Jamaica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/jamaica' },
  { title: 'Bahamas for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahamas' },
  { title: 'Panama for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/panama' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'barbadosFit', header: 'Barbados Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BBD$980-1,400/mo', barbadosFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BBD$1,150-1,640/mo', barbadosFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BBD$880-1,255/mo', barbadosFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BBD$820-1,170/mo', barbadosFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Sagicor (Local)', entryAge: '69', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BBD$500-900/mo', barbadosFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BBD$880-1,400', annual: 'BBD$10,560-16,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BBD$1,210-1,870', annual: 'BBD$14,520-22,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BBD$1,630-2,510', annual: 'BBD$19,560-30,120' },
  { category: 'Local Private Insurance', monthly: 'BBD$500-900/mo', annual: 'BBD$6,000-10,800' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'BBD$1,500-3,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Barbados 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Barbados. Caribbean paradise, British heritage, excellent beaches, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Barbados"
  subheadline="Barbados offers Caribbean paradise with British heritage, stable democracy, excellent beaches, and English language—a sophisticated island destination for retirement."
  heroImage="/images/countries/barbados-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Barbados</h2>
  <p>
    Barbados offers Caribbean beauty with British sophistication—stable government, excellent infrastructure, English language, and no hurricane damage for decades. For those seeking Caribbean retirement with first-world standards, Barbados delivers though at premium cost.
  </p>

  <p>
    The West Coast (Platinum Coast) offers luxury living and expat communities. South Coast provides more affordable options with good beaches. Bridgetown has capital amenities. Christ Church offers retirement communities. The entire island is small (166 sq miles) and accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good for Caribbean; Queen Elizabeth Hospital</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BBD$6,000-12,000/month (~$3,000-6,000); high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; year-round warmth; outside hurricane belt</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> British heritage; sophisticated; friendly</li>
      <li><strong>Retirement Program:</strong> Welcome Stamp allows remote work/retirement</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Barbados Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Barbados has the best healthcare in the Eastern Caribbean—Queen Elizabeth Hospital is the main public facility. Sandy Crest Medical Centre and Bayview Hospital are private options. Most specialties available locally; complex cases may require travel to Miami or elsewhere.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is subsidized for residents. Private facilities offer shorter waits and better amenities. Many specialists trained in UK, US, or Canada. Evacuation to Miami (4-hour flight) available for complex cases. Overall, good for Caribbean standards.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Good for Caribbean</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Barbados healthcare exceeds most Caribbean islands but isn't Miami or London. Complex oncology, specialized surgery, and rare conditions may require travel. Private insurance ensuring US evacuation recommended for comprehensive coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Barbados offers retirement-friendly options:
  </p>

  <h3>Barbados Welcome Stamp</h3>
  <p>
    12-month visa for remote workers and retirees. Income requirement $50,000/year for individuals, $70,000 for families. Renewable. Very popular since 2020.
  </p>

  <h3>Special Entry Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with assets/income. Leads to permanent residence. Demonstrate financial independence.
  </p>

  <h3>Immigrant Status</h3>
  <p>
    After 5 years residence, can apply for immigrant status. Various categories including retired persons.
  </p>

  <h3>UK/CARICOM Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Special arrangements exist for UK citizens and CARICOM member nationals.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Barbados:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Welcome Stamp:</strong> Health insurance required (coverage in Barbados)</li>
    <li><strong>Special Entry Permit:</strong> Insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical necessity:</strong> Private coverage essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> US/UK coverage for complex conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Barbados</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International coverage recommended for quality care and evacuation. Local options (Sagicor) work for routine care. Ensure plan covers treatment in Miami/US for complex conditions. Caribbean plans often exclude US coverage—verify this for seniors.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Barbados, coverage with US access recommended:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Barbados</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Caribbean + US coverage, good network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Sagicor:</strong> Major regional insurer, local expertise</li>
    <li><strong>US access:</strong> Critical for complex conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage options including US evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Barbados reflect Caribbean rates:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sagicor local:</strong> Lower cost for routine care coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce monthly premiums</li>
    <li><strong>US-excluding plans:</strong> Cheaper but risky for complex needs</li>
    <li><strong>Annual payment:</strong> Some insurers offer discounts</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £3,500/month pension. Welcome Stamp. West Coast.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with UK and US coverage. Commonwealth comfort.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BBD$1,300/month. Caribbean living; UK/US backup healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Snowbird, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $5,000/month income. Welcome Stamp. Christ Church.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Americas coverage. Medicare for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BBD$1,500/month. Island escape; easy Miami evacuation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Expatriate, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> C$4,500/month pension. Special Entry Permit. South Coast.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care international + maintain provincial coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BBD$1,000/month. Caribbean warmth; Canadian backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Barbados expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among the most expensive Caribbean destinations. Housing, imported goods, and dining are costly. Budget BBD$6,000-12,000/month minimum for comfortable living. Quality comes at a price; those seeking budget Caribbean should look elsewhere.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Barbados safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of the safest Caribbean islands. Low violent crime; petty theft exists. Stable democracy with strong rule of law. British heritage means familiar systems. Generally safe for walking and exploring.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricanes?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Barbados is outside main hurricane belt—last major hit was 1955. Location in far southeastern Caribbean provides protection. Still prepare for tropical weather but significantly lower risk than other Caribbean islands.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Medicare in Barbados?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No—Medicare doesn't cover overseas. Need separate international insurance. However, Medicare can cover you during US visits, which pairs well with international plan for Barbados.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Caribbean coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Barbados authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
